    "rawCode": "N400",
    "shortDesc": "Benign prostatic hyperplasia without lower urinry tract symp",
    "longDesc": "Benign prostatic hyperplasia without lower urinary tract symptoms",
    "plainEnglish": "Benign prostatic hyperplasia (BPH) is a non-cancerous enlargement of the prostate gland, a walnut-sized organ in men that produces fluid for semen. In this case, the prostate has grown larger than normal, but the person is not experiencing any bothersome urinary symptoms like difficulty urinating, frequent urination, or weak urine flow. This is often discovered incidentally during routine checkups or imaging for other reasons.",
    "whoUses": "Urologists and primary care physicians use this code when documenting enlarged prostates found on examination or imaging in asymptomatic men, typically during preventive care or workups for unrelated conditions. This code appears on EOB statements when men have prostate exams, PSA tests, or imaging studies that reveal enlargement without symptoms, and it often does not require immediate treatment since no bothersome symptoms are present.",
