    "rawCode": "N6310",
    "shortDesc": "Unspecified lump in the right breast, unspecified quadrant",
    "longDesc": "Unspecified lump in the right breast, unspecified quadrant",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a lump or mass that has been found in the right breast, but the doctor hasn't yet determined which specific area of the breast it's in or what's causing it. The lump could be felt or seen on imaging, but further testing is needed to figure out if it's something serious like cancer or just a benign (non-cancerous) cyst or tissue growth.",
    "whoUses": "Breast surgeons, oncologists, and general practitioners use this code when a patient reports or is found to have a breast lump that requires evaluation. It commonly appears on EOB statements as an initial diagnostic code that typically leads to imaging studies (mammograms or ultrasounds) and possible biopsy to determine the nature of the lump.",
