    "shortDesc": "Excessive and frequent menstruation with regular cycle",
    "longDesc": "Excessive and frequent menstruation with regular cycle",
    "plainEnglish": "This condition means a woman has abnormally heavy menstrual bleeding during her period, even though her periods arrive on a regular, predictable schedule. The bleeding is so excessive that it may require frequent changes of pads or tampons, last longer than normal, or cause symptoms like fatigue and anemia from blood loss. While the timing of periods is normal, the amount of blood lost is significantly more than typical.",
    "whoUses": "Gynecologists and primary care physicians use this code when evaluating excessive menstrual bleeding. It commonly appears on EOB statements when patients seek treatment for heavy periods and may be documented during initial evaluation before further testing or intervention is performed.",
